## Domain / Build — export the live build log to a .log file

Context: The Building Digital Twin panel added earlier today shows
each phase live, but the data was trapped in the DOM — users who
wanted to share a slow build with us had to screenshot the panel
or copy-paste row by row. Asked for a one-click way to dump the
log to a text file.

The new **Export** button sits in the panel header next to the
total-duration label and the dismiss-X. It becomes enabled the
moment the first poll lands (so the user can save mid-build) and
stays enabled after the build finishes, so they can come back to
the page and grab the log even after the wall timer stopped
ticking. Output is plain text — no JSON, no CSV — so it pastes
straight into a Slack thread or a JIRA comment.

Changes:

1. src/front/templates/partials/dtwin/_query_sync.html
   - New `#syncBuildLogExport` button (`btn-outline-secondary`,
     `bi-download` icon, "Export" label) inserted between the
     total-duration small text and the existing X dismiss button.
     Starts `disabled` so it can't be clicked before any data has
     been rendered.

2. src/front/static/query/js/query-sync.js
   - New module-local `_syncBuildLogLastTask` cache. `showBuildLog`
     resets it to `null` and disables the button; `renderBuildLog`
     stores the latest poll payload and re-enables the button. We
     keep the last task around for the lifetime of the section, so
     hitting Export after the build has finished still works.
   - New `exportBuildLog()` builds a UTF-8 `Blob`, derives the
     filename from `task.started_at` (`digital-twin-build_<iso
     timestamp>.log`), and triggers the download via a transient
     `<a>` element + `URL.revokeObjectURL` cleanup.
   - New `_formatBuildLogAsText(task)` produces a three-block log:
     a header with task ID / name / status / created /
     started / completed / total duration / progress / last
     message / error; a `Steps` block with one entry per step
     showing `[NN] STATUS  description`, the started/completed
