## Digital Twin build — fast gzip, background Volume archive, optional skip

Context: The final *Backing up the graph to the registry* phase was the
dominant wall-clock cost on large graphs: ``tarfile`` at gzip level 9
buffered the entire archive in RAM, then a single UC Files API upload
blocked ``complete_task`` — the UI showed "running" for minutes after
the graph was already correct under ``/tmp/ontobricks``.  Users also
asked for a way to skip the Volume upload when iterating locally.

The fix has three parts:

1. **Fast gzip** — ``GraphSyncService.sync_to_volume`` now calls
   ``tarfile.open(..., mode="w:gz", compresslevel=1)`` (default),
   with timing logs split between compress and upload.  The static
   helper ``upload_to_volume`` forwards ``compresslevel`` (default
   ``1``).

2. **Background archive** — For session builds with
   ``archive_to_registry=True`` (default), after the snapshot step the
   worker calls ``advance_step`` into the archive row, starts a
   **daemon** ``threading.Thread`` that runs the existing
   ``Domain.sync_ladybug_to_volume`` + existence-cache update, then
   immediately calls the new ``TaskManager.complete_current_step`` so
   the archive row shows **completed** while the upload continues.
   ``complete_task`` runs right after; the completion message appends
   *"Registry backup continues in the background."*  The task result
   dict gains ``archive_to_registry`` and ``archive_background: true``.

3. **Checkbox** — Under *Build mode* on Domain / Build, a new
   **Archive graph to registry** checkbox (default **on**) posts
   ``archive_to_registry`` in the ``POST /dtwin/sync/start`` JSON body.
   When **off**, ``run_build_task`` ``advance_step`` + ``skip_step``
   marks the archive row as skipped with a plain-English reason; the
   result dict includes ``archive_skipped: true``.  External REST
   builds expose the same flag on ``BuildRequest`` (Pydantic default
   ``True``) for forward compatibility even though the API build path
   does not execute the session-only archive block today.

Supporting change: ``TaskManager.complete_current_step`` marks the
current running step completed and increments ``current_step`` without
starting the next step — the missing primitive for "UI phase done,
async work continues".

Changes:

1. src/back/core/graphdb/ladybugdb/GraphSyncService.py
   - ``sync_to_volume(..., compresslevel=1)`` — docstring explains the
     trade-off; structured log lines for archive size / compress time /
     upload time.
   - ``upload_to_volume(..., compresslevel=1)`` passes the kwarg through.

2. src/back/core/task_manager/TaskManager.py
   - New ``complete_current_step(task_id, message=None)``.

3. src/back/objects/digitaltwin/DigitalTwin.py
   - ``run_build_task(..., *, archive_to_registry=True)`` — session-only
     archive branch rewritten per above; ``result_data`` extended;
     completion message suffix when archiving.

4. src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py
   - Reads ``archive_to_registry`` from JSON (default ``True``) and
     passes it into ``run_build_task``.

5. src/api/routers/digitaltwin.py
   - ``BuildRequest.archive_to_registry`` field + pass-through to
     ``run_build_task``.

6. src/front/templates/partials/dtwin/_query_sync.html
