## Build log UI — honest timing for background registry archive

Context: After moving the LadybugDB → Volume upload into a daemon thread,
the archive ``TaskStep`` is marked completed in the same millisecond it
is started (``complete_current_step`` immediately after ``advance_step``).
The Domain / Build log panel therefore showed **0ms** next to *Backing up
the graph to the registry*, which looked like a bug even though the
heavy work was still running asynchronously.

The fix is presentation-only: when ``step.name === "archive"`` and
``task.result.archive_background`` is true, the time column shows
**Continues after build** (with a tooltip) instead of a misleading
duration, a short explanatory line appears under the step title, and the
exported ``.log`` replaces the bogus duration line with an explicit note
that the registry copy continues in the background.

